{ After Black has accepted the sacrifice, the main idea is to develop our pieces very quickly and start attacking Black's weaknesses  (mainly f7)  . While doing this, we attack the g4-knight giving us an even further development lead. In addition, 5... Nxg4 opens the g-file for our rook to pressure g7 - making it hard for Black to complete his development. }
6... exd4
{ The downside of this move is that Black is opening the center where White will be more developed and coordinated. }
7. Nxd4 Nge5
{ Black thinks that the knight is safe here as  8.f4  can't be played in the view of  ...Qh4+.  This is true but there is another way for White  ! }
8. Bg5
{ White challenges the queen on d8 and asks Black how he is going to keep her safe. }
8... Nf6 9. Qe2
