[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "3. Ch.2 Declining the sacrifice"]
[Black "101. Declining the sacrifice: 5... g6"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. g4
{ Let's check what happens if Black refuses to take the pawn. For me it's enough that the position will be tactically complex with equal material but of course I need to show something. }
5... g6 6. g5
{ Pushing Black's knight to an uncomfortable square on the edge of the board while gaining space. }
6... Nh5
{ The computer gives an edge for White here and suggests many times to exchange on e5. I prefer to keep the tension and play as suggested, because most of the time the engine changes its mind in the end. }
7. Be3 c6 8. Qd2 Qc7 9. O-O-O Be7 10. Ne2
{ White is almost fully developed and ready to challenge the h5-Knight with Ng3 if Black castles short. }
