[Black "145. Different move orders: 3... Nf6"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5
{ 1...d6  is the best way for Black if he wishes to play the Philidor Defence. }
2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 Nf6 4. dxe5
{ If you don't like to enter such positions, you can transpose to our mainline with  4.Nc3. }
4... Nxe4 5. Qd5 Nc5 6. Bg5 { Developing with a threat. } 6... Be7 7. exd6
{ Exchanging pawns to defend our g5 bishop with no loss time by opening the way for our queen. }
7... Qxd6 8. Nc3
{ Again not losing time by running, just developing and protecting. } 8... Be6
9. Qxd6
{ Okay now forgive me please don't develop and protect with Bc4. Our Queen is too important to us to lose it for a bishop. }
9... Bxd6 10. Nb5
{ Black is forced now to give us the d6-bishop in order not to lose the c7-pawn. White will have the two bishops and a comfortable game. }
