1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 Nd7 4. Bc4 Be7
{ Even a 2300 player didn't notice the danger of this move order. } 5. dxe5
Nxe5 6. Nxe5 dxe5 7. Qh5 g6 8. Qxe5 Nf6 9. Bh6 Rg8
{ The following few moves show what happens when you know you have a winning position, and instead of focusing on the position you start looking at the games of your teammates and drinking your coffee ! }
10. h3
{ This throws half of my advantage away. I didn't spend much time and I decided not to calculate Black's possibility of ...Ng4, instead just preventing that idea.   10.Nc3 !  This is much stronger as having quick development is worth much more than the bishop pair.  Ng4  11.Qf4  Nxh6  12.Qxh6  Qd4  13.Bb3  +- }
10... Qd6 11. Qxd6 Bxd6 12. O-O
{ I was just dreaming about e4-e5, thinking that I would win easily with that. }
12... Be6 13. Bxe6 fxe6 14. Re1 Be5 15. c3 g5
{ I have no idea why I completely forgot about this move. Now I had to spend 20 minutes to find the only moves, luckily there was a way. }
16. Nd2 { 16.h4 ?  gxh4  Now White has to struggle for a draw. } 16... Nh5
{ 16...Rg6  Black's initial idea is refuted now:  17.Nf3 !  Bf4  18.h4 !  Rxh6   18...g4  19.Bxf4  gxf3  20.g3  19.hxg5  Bxg5  20.Nxg5  White solved all his problems and kept his extra pawn. }
17. Bxg5 Rxg5 18. Nf3 Bf6
{ Giving me an extra tempo for no reason.   18...Bf4  was better, but White is clearly better anyway:  19.Nxg5  Bxg5  ± }
19. e5 { Always look for in-between moves ! } 19... Be7 20. Nxg5 Bxg5 21. g3
{ 21.g4 ?  This gives up control over the f4-square, and with it the advantage.  Nf4 }
21... Be7 22. Rad1 Ng7 23. g4
{ Now this is possible as Black can't stop f2-f4.   23...Bg5  is simply met with  24.Re4. }
23... a5 24. f4 Ra6 25. Kg2 b5 26. Kf3 Rc6 27. Ke4
{ Using all my pieces. My king is maximally centralized as there is no danger of being checkmated at all. }
27... b4 28. f5 { The rest is easy. } 28... Bh4 29. Re3 exf5+ 30. gxf5 Rc4+ 31.
Rd4 Rc5 32. Red3 Nh5 33. cxb4 axb4 34. Rxb4 Ng3+ 35. Kf4 Ne2+ 36. Kg4 Bf2 37.
e6 Rc1 38. Rb8+ Ke7 39. Rd7+ Kf6 40. Rf8+ Ke5 41. e7 Rc4+ 42. Kf3 *

